♪ Dah dah nah nah nah ♪

02:04.004 --> 02:05.004
What?

02:09.863 --> 02:11.952
- I know, it's just--

02:11.953 --> 02:13.036
- What is it?

02:14.690 --> 02:16.133
- I'm scared, Matthew.

02:18.250 --> 02:19.953
I just want you to come back.

02:22.787 --> 02:24.870
- Then let's get married.

02:25.806 --> 02:28.441
Marry me.

02:28.442 --> 02:29.442
- What?

02:31.995 --> 02:32.995
- Marry me.

02:34.136 --> 02:35.803
- Matthew, are you serious?

02:36.705 --> 02:41.043
- I don't have a ring,
but I'll get you one.

02:41.044 --> 02:43.176
- I don't know what to say.

02:43.177 --> 02:44.177
- Say yes.

02:47.972 --> 02:49.408
- Okay.

02:49.409 --> 02:50.317
- Okay?

02:50.318 --> 02:53.229
- Yes, I'll marry you!
- Okay!

02:53.230 --> 02:54.273
- Oh my gosh!

02:57.760 --> 02:58.760
- Let's do it now.

02:59.575 --> 03:01.549
- Right here?
- Right here.

03:01.550 --> 03:02.559
Right now.

03:02.560 --> 03:04.329
- Are you serious?
- Yes.

03:04.330 --> 03:05.613
- No, really?

03:07.040 --> 03:10.249
- Dearly beloved, we're
gathered here today

03:10.250 --> 03:13.393
for the union of Matthew and Scarlett.

03:14.840 --> 03:16.929
Matthew, do you take Scarlett

03:16.930 --> 03:18.563
to be your lawfully wedded wife?

03:23.654 --> 03:24.654
I do.

03:26.861 --> 03:30.200
And do you, Scarlett, take Matthew

03:30.201 --> 03:33.118
to be your lawfully wedded husband?

03:34.980 --> 03:36.029
- I do.

03:41.315 --> 03:45.482
- Scarlett, I will protect
you and provide for you

03:46.930 --> 03:51.779
from this day forth through
sickness and in health,

03:51.780 --> 03:54.749
through the good times and the bad times,

03:54.750 --> 03:56.327
for richer or poorer,

03:58.870 --> 04:01.790
from today until death do us part.

04:06.486 --> 04:11.486
- Matthew, I promise to care for you

04:12.610 --> 04:16.512
and to love you through
sickness and in health,

04:17.410 --> 04:18.660
through richer or poorer,

04:19.550 --> 04:22.253
for the rest of my life
until the day I die.

04:26.720 --> 04:28.721
- Well, kiss the bride already!

04:37.085 --> 04:38.085
- Oh!

04:41.980 --> 04:42.980
Give me your hand.

04:46.124 --> 04:47.124
Boop!

04:48.763 --> 04:49.812
There you go.

04:49.813 --> 04:53.143
Now you are officially my husband.

04:54.320 --> 04:59.320
- I'll never take it off.

05:03.813 --> 05:05.063
I have something for you.

05:06.344 --> 05:07.594
- You do?
- Turn around.

05:10.102 --> 05:11.102
- Okay.

05:13.460 --> 05:15.923
- Don't look.
- I won't, I won't.

05:16.940 --> 05:19.703
You have one minute, Matthew.

05:32.162 --> 05:33.329
Are you ready?

05:34.374 --> 05:36.374
- Turn around.

05:41.080 --> 05:42.080
- What's this?

05:43.180 --> 05:45.713
- My grandmother loved red ribbon,

05:47.400 --> 05:50.599
and whenever I see it I think of her,

05:50.600 --> 05:54.159
so I made you this so
that when you wear it

05:54.160 --> 05:55.643
you can think of me.

06:06.792 --> 06:07.792
- I love it.

06:12.386 --> 06:14.053
- Don't take it off.

06:14.900 --> 06:15.900
- Never.

06:22.334 --> 06:23.600
Woo!

06:23.601 --> 06:25.386
- Woo!
- We're married!

06:25.387 --> 06:27.404
- Woo woo woo woo woo!

08:02.128 --> 08:02.961
- Scarlett?

08:02.962 --> 08:03.969
It's Mother.

08:03.970 --> 08:06.169
Why is this door closed?

08:06.170 --> 08:07.003
- Just a second!

08:07.004 --> 08:08.869
- What are you doing
up in your room all day?

08:08.870 --> 08:10.079
Open this door.

08:11.920 --> 08:12.920
- I just...

08:14.690 --> 08:15.898
It's open.

08:17.800 --> 08:21.319
- I don't know why
doors are closed in my house.

08:21.320 --> 08:22.320
- Hey.

08:25.243 --> 08:26.243
- Ooh.

08:28.470 --> 08:31.199
My shoulder, it hurts so much.

08:31.200 --> 08:32.190
You know, that rivet gun,

08:32.191 --> 08:34.149
it just vibrates all day.

08:34.150 --> 08:36.399
It's more than I bargained for.

08:36.400 --> 08:38.429
- I could get you some water.

08:38.429 --> 08:40.832
Or some milk with, would
you like some milk?

08:42.320 --> 08:44.058
- Milk would be lovely.

08:44.059 --> 08:44.893
- I'll be right back.

08:44.894 --> 08:47.263
- What have you been doing
with yourself all day?

08:49.080 --> 08:50.972
- Oh, you know, just,

08:53.590 --> 08:54.462
the usual.

08:54.463 --> 08:56.709
- You know, the men are down at the front,

08:56.710 --> 08:59.249
the women have to go down
to the factories and work.

08:59.250 --> 09:00.449
The more of us that pitch in,

09:00.450 --> 09:03.063
the sooner the soldiers will be back.

09:04.080 --> 09:05.080
- I know, Mom.

09:10.220 --> 09:11.543
- There's nothing in this.

09:13.030 --> 09:14.130
What are you thinking?

09:15.160 --> 09:16.160
- I'm sorry.

09:17.400 --> 09:19.209
I'm, I'm not thinking clearly, okay?

09:19.210 --> 09:20.460
I really don't feel well.

09:23.330 --> 09:27.703
I just have these headaches, and nausea.

09:28.578 --> 09:30.128
- Well, maybe you have the flu.

09:31.930 --> 09:33.669
- It's going around, right?

09:33.670 --> 09:34.670
- So I hear.

09:35.432 --> 09:37.139
But we all need to do our part.

09:37.140 --> 09:39.090
If you haven't heard, there's a war on.

09:41.530 --> 09:42.530
- Mom,

09:43.750 --> 09:44.610
that reminds me.

09:44.611 --> 09:45.939
I have a question.

09:45.940 --> 09:46.773
- I'm your mother.

09:46.774 --> 09:47.853
You can ask me anything.

09:49.200 --> 09:53.033
- Okay, well, it's kinda personal, okay?

09:54.830 --> 09:56.829
It's about my period.

09:56.830 --> 09:58.259
- Menstruation, Scarlett.

09:58.260 --> 09:59.180
Women menstruate.

09:59.181 --> 10:00.800
- Right, menstruation.

10:05.601 --> 10:09.101
Okay, I don't really know how to ask this.

10:12.350 --> 10:16.523
When you're on your menstrual cycle,

10:17.860 --> 10:20.060
are you supposed to
start every month, like,

10:21.720 --> 10:22.929
on the dot?

10:22.930 --> 10:24.739
- I'm sure there's a book at the library.

10:24.740 --> 10:25.573
You can look up--

10:25.574 --> 10:27.329
- Mom, I really would rather just ask you

10:27.330 --> 10:28.739
than go all the way down to the library.

10:28.740 --> 10:31.729
- Yes, a woman menstruates every 28 days.

10:31.730 --> 10:32.943
Next subject.

10:37.950 --> 10:38.950
- Okay.

10:40.040 --> 10:44.783
So what if they're late a couple weeks?

10:46.610 --> 10:48.213
- That's not a problem.

10:49.220 --> 10:50.289
- A month?

10:50.290 --> 10:52.109
- Well, I would go to the doctor.

10:52.110 --> 10:54.060
Why are you, who are you talking about?

10:55.790 --> 10:56.790
- A friend.

10:58.510 --> 10:59.510
- What friend?

11:00.550 --> 11:03.449
- Just someone that I've been
friends with for a while.

11:03.450 --> 11:04.450
That's all.

11:06.100 --> 11:10.383
- I would not associate with
this loose girl any longer.

11:14.080 --> 11:16.133
It's like Nicole across the street.

11:17.250 --> 11:20.359
Her boyfriend and her decided
to have premarital sex

11:20.360 --> 11:24.099
and he went off to the front
line, got himself killed,

11:24.100 --> 11:26.949
and now she's at home
with a baby, not married.

11:26.950 --> 11:28.239
How is she gonna afford that?

11:28.240 --> 11:29.853
You're lucky you're not her.

11:32.200 --> 11:33.903
Why are you so upset?

11:36.190 --> 11:37.433
How old is this girl?

11:41.170 --> 11:42.663
- Her birthday's next week.

11:45.780 --> 11:48.282
- Is this some roundabout way to tell me

11:48.283 --> 11:49.523
that you're pregnant?

11:55.530 --> 11:56.530
- Yeah.

11:58.920 --> 12:00.282
- I did not raise you like that.

12:00.283 --> 12:02.169
- I didn't plan this!

12:02.170 --> 12:03.170
- Apparently not.

12:04.375 --> 12:06.429
- Look, I know you're disappointed,

12:06.430 --> 12:09.389
but I am so scared.

12:09.390 --> 12:10.453
- Who is this boy?

12:11.430 --> 12:12.430
What's his name?

12:14.290 --> 12:15.329
- His name's Matthew.

12:15.330 --> 12:16.163
- Matthew.

12:16.164 --> 12:18.333
And where is this Matthew?

12:22.700 --> 12:24.200
- He's at the front line, Mom.

12:33.700 --> 12:36.159
- Well, we're gonna take care of this,

12:36.160 --> 12:37.959
and what we're gonna do

12:37.960 --> 12:40.519
is we're going to send you off to a home

12:40.520 --> 12:42.002
for unwed mothers--
- What?

12:42.003 --> 12:43.089
Mom, no!

12:43.090 --> 12:45.489
I'm not gonna give my
child up for adoption.

12:45.490 --> 12:46.689
- You'll have the baby there.

12:46.690 --> 12:50.239
Some nice family will give it a good home

12:50.240 --> 12:51.559
who can afford a baby.

12:51.560 --> 12:53.603
- This is my child we're talking about.

12:55.030 --> 12:56.563
Your grandchild!

12:59.580 --> 13:01.189
What, are you honestly telling me

13:01.190 --> 13:05.209
that you'd be okay with me having a child

13:05.210 --> 13:06.973
and giving them up for adoption?

13:07.920 --> 13:09.863
And you never knowing your grandchild?

13:11.570 --> 13:12.570
Never,

13:14.770 --> 13:16.620
never knowing how they grew up to be?

13:21.650 --> 13:23.300
Would you have done that with me?

13:27.730 --> 13:30.059
- We'll go to the pastor and we'll see

13:30.060 --> 13:31.793
if he has an answer for us.

13:33.280 --> 13:37.073
It's different now, because
the boys are at war.

13:39.620 --> 13:41.470
We'll figure out what to do together.

13:44.070 --> 13:45.093
Get dressed, honey.

13:46.640 --> 13:48.033
We're goin' to church.

14:04.870 --> 14:06.823
Go practice your guitar, Owen.

14:08.840 --> 14:10.096
30 minutes.

14:21.500 --> 14:22.509
Pick the guitar up.

14:22.510 --> 14:24.373
Let's get moving.

14:25.400 --> 14:27.059
- 20 minutes?

14:27.060 --> 14:27.910
- You know the drill.

14:27.911 --> 14:29.499
We do this every day.

14:29.500 --> 14:30.643
- 21 minutes?

14:31.705 --> 14:33.556
- Well, if you
wanna get good at something

14:33.557 --> 14:35.809
you need to practice.

14:35.810 --> 14:37.133
Practice makes perfect.

14:41.150 --> 14:42.519
Thank you.

14:42.520 --> 14:44.283
- But Grandma, I'm tired.

14:46.641 --> 14:48.593
- You practice your guitar, please.

14:50.110 --> 14:51.639
Grandma has all this sewing she has to do

14:51.640 --> 14:52.640
for Aunt Milly.

14:57.461 --> 15:00.409
Play me that song that they taught you.

15:00.410 --> 15:01.653
You remember.

15:03.102 --> 15:06.519
(guitar strings twanging

15:27.130 --> 15:28.689
What's that?

15:28.690 --> 15:30.454
- I can't play the guitar.

15:30.455 --> 15:31.370
The string's broken.

15:31.371 --> 15:34.999
- Honey, I told you, you need
to take care of your things.

15:35.000 --> 15:36.293
- I have some money.

15:37.180 --> 15:40.093
- It's a really valuable
instrument in this family.

15:41.070 --> 15:43.870
- Oh, Grandma, can you read
this letter from my teacher?

15:45.430 --> 15:46.880
- A letter from your teacher?

15:48.610 --> 15:49.910
What did you do this time?

15:51.290 --> 15:53.023
This is all Grandma needs today.

15:54.200 --> 15:55.600
Well, I hope it's good news.

15:57.950 --> 16:02.950
Dear Owen and family, you and
all your family and friends

16:04.260 --> 16:06.489
are cordially invited to join the school

16:06.490 --> 16:10.583
for cookies and photographs,

16:11.800 --> 16:13.389
tomorrow.

16:13.390 --> 16:15.623
Well, isn't that nice.

16:17.460 --> 16:21.833
We can go have a family
photo together, all of us.

16:24.395 --> 16:25.395
- All?

16:27.825 --> 16:31.579
- All is you and me.

16:31.580 --> 16:32.923
That's all.

16:34.610 --> 16:39.187
But what I think they
meant is all your family,

16:42.310 --> 16:46.489
your mom and your dad,

16:46.490 --> 16:49.723
and your grandma, you.

16:57.670 --> 16:59.233
- Where are your parents?

17:01.613 --> 17:04.280
- Well,

17:07.609 --> 17:08.609
they're in heaven.

17:11.916 --> 17:13.213
- Is heaven fun?

17:17.980 --> 17:19.423
- It's a very fun place.

17:21.010 --> 17:24.032
- Then why don't you go to heaven?

17:24.034 --> 17:26.989
- Well, then I would miss out

17:26.990 --> 17:28.903
on raising you every day, wouldn't I?

17:33.430 --> 17:35.427
- Are my parents in heaven?

17:38.127 --> 17:39.127
- No, Owen.

17:45.703 --> 17:49.066
I don't know where they are, honey.

17:49.067 --> 17:50.917
- Then why don't they come to see me?

17:55.270 --> 17:56.770
- I don't know where they are,

17:58.230 --> 18:01.293
but I'm sure they wish they were here.

18:04.200 --> 18:07.516
And someday, they might come here

18:07.517 --> 18:11.483
and just surprise you,
and surprise me too.

18:13.730 --> 18:15.093
They will come in the door,

18:19.140 --> 18:20.290
and we'll see your mom.

18:23.450 --> 18:24.533
And your dad.

18:26.930 --> 18:28.973
And they're gonna give you a big hug.

18:35.180 --> 18:37.259
- Why don't they just come now?

18:37.260 --> 18:38.689
I don't want a surprise.

18:38.690 --> 18:41.253
I just want them to be here.

18:44.350 --> 18:46.209
- I would do anything I could

18:46.210 --> 18:48.323
to get them here for you, Owen.

18:49.599 --> 18:50.599
Anything.

19:03.601 --> 19:05.184
What are you doing?

19:06.116 --> 19:07.116
- Mom?

19:08.906 --> 19:09.906
Dad?

19:14.108 --> 19:15.275
Are you there?

19:19.056 --> 19:21.025
I really miss you.

19:21.026 --> 19:22.217
Are you there?

19:22.218 --> 19:25.976
If you can hear me, please say something.

19:25.977 --> 19:27.394
- Get down.

19:28.980 --> 19:29.980
- Dad?

19:31.331 --> 19:32.331
Dad!

19:38.565 --> 19:41.560
Why won't you pick up the phone?

19:41.561 --> 19:42.561
- Oh, Owen.

19:50.458 --> 19:51.708
Owen, get down.

19:54.963 --> 19:56.729
Owen, your parents aren't in a place

19:56.730 --> 20:00.120
that you can reach them.

20:09.370 --> 20:12.993
Now, enough of this.

20:14.490 --> 20:16.159
We need to stick to the plan.

20:16.160 --> 20:19.403
- Grandma, I wanna see my parents.

20:20.790 --> 20:22.973
- Owen, please.

20:24.360 --> 20:26.259
You need to go take a bath.

20:26.260 --> 20:28.469
- Please, I just wanna
stay up a little later.

20:28.470 --> 20:30.473
- You have to get up early for school.

20:33.410 --> 20:35.429
Please, Owen!

20:35.430 --> 20:38.179
You are giving me a
really hard time tonight,

20:38.180 --> 20:39.239
and you know what,

20:39.240 --> 20:41.629
I'm gonna go give you
a hard time tomorrow.

20:41.630 --> 20:44.369
I'm gonna go to that school
with my biggest funny red hat

20:44.370 --> 20:46.199
and my biggest funny red shoes

20:46.200 --> 20:47.459
and I'm gonna walk in there

20:47.460 --> 20:49.189
and I'm gonna have a big sign

20:49.190 --> 20:51.393
and I'm gonna yell that
I'm Owen's grandma.

20:53.175 --> 20:54.503
- Okay, I'll take a bath.

21:02.350 --> 21:03.909
- Goodnight, Owen.

21:03.910 --> 21:05.723
I love you very much.

21:13.760 --> 21:15.523
My sweet prince.

21:18.340 --> 21:19.340
When you wake up,

21:22.470 --> 21:24.293
Grandma's gonna have a surprise.

21:34.160 --> 21:36.097
I'm gonna go find your mom and dad.

21:39.620 --> 21:41.420
And I'm gonna bring 'em back to you.

21:44.887 --> 21:48.320
And I'm not gonna let
you down one day more.

21:52.099 --> 21:54.016
I love you, sweet Owen.

22:57.875 --> 23:00.708
- Grandma's been gone for one day,

23:02.238 --> 23:05.615
two days, three days, four days,

23:05.616 --> 23:08.939
five days, six days, seven days,

23:08.940 --> 23:13.023
eight days, nine days, 10
days, 11 days, 12 days,

23:15.536 --> 23:16.536
13.

23:45.898 --> 23:47.167
- Owen!

23:47.168 --> 23:48.251
It's me, Zoe.

23:49.428 --> 23:50.428
Coming in.

23:58.022 --> 23:59.022
Owen?

24:00.550 --> 24:01.779
Huh.

24:01.780 --> 24:04.197
I wonder where Owen could be.

24:06.748 --> 24:07.748
Hmm.

24:08.700 --> 24:10.179
Well, if he's not here,

24:10.180 --> 24:12.654
I guess I'll just leave.

24:12.655 --> 24:13.738
- Zoe!

24:17.840 --> 24:18.840
Boo!

24:20.103 --> 24:21.572
- What are you doing?

24:21.573 --> 24:24.035
- I was hiding 'cause
no one comes to see me.

24:24.036 --> 24:27.823
- No one comes to see you,
what are you talkin' about?

24:27.824 --> 24:28.657
Be careful.

24:28.658 --> 24:29.757
Come here.

24:32.086 --> 24:33.859
- Woo!

24:33.860 --> 24:36.269
- Oh my goodness!
- Again, again, again!

24:36.270 --> 24:37.773
- Okay, this way.
- One more.

24:37.774 --> 24:39.559
- Here we go.

24:39.560 --> 24:41.114
- Okay, one more, one more, one more.

24:41.115 --> 24:41.948
- Okay, woo!

24:41.949 --> 24:43.539
One more.

24:43.540 --> 24:44.540
Ohh, okay.

24:47.227 --> 24:50.296
Ooh!

24:50.297 --> 24:52.009
You are heavy!

24:52.010 --> 24:53.063
Wow, you've grown.

24:54.357 --> 24:55.357
Woo!

25:00.899 --> 25:02.066
Oh, come here.

25:03.060 --> 25:04.050
I missed you.

25:04.051 --> 25:06.351
- I missed you too.

25:06.352 --> 25:07.893
- Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas.

25:08.920 --> 25:10.209
- I'm going out with my friends tonight

25:10.210 --> 25:13.523
for a little special thing,
but I did get you a present.

25:17.110 --> 25:18.443
Merry Christmas!

25:21.688 --> 25:22.688
- Thanks!

25:31.460 --> 25:32.460
Wait a minute.

25:37.660 --> 25:39.479
This is the exact same wrapping paper

25:39.480 --> 25:41.633
I got last year from Santa.

25:43.970 --> 25:45.633
Are you Santa?

25:46.750 --> 25:47.750
- No.

25:48.430 --> 25:50.703
Maybe he has the same wrapping paper.

25:52.620 --> 25:53.773
- Let me check.

25:53.774 --> 25:54.774
- Okay.

25:59.580 --> 26:00.580
- It's gone.

26:01.800 --> 26:04.732
- Well, I'm not Santa Claus, so.

26:04.733 --> 26:07.399
