32:29.760 --> 32:32.399
- I don't normally drink, I promise.

32:32.400 --> 32:35.069
- I believe you.

32:35.070 --> 32:36.767
Let me go get you some milk.

32:36.768 --> 32:37.601
- No!

32:37.601 --> 32:38.434
Wait.

32:38.435 --> 32:40.849
Milk, milk makes you so fat.

32:40.850 --> 32:42.699
- Oh, but it'll help your tummy.

32:42.700 --> 32:44.540
I'm going to go get it for you.

32:44.541 --> 32:45.624
- Okay, okay.

32:50.800 --> 32:52.149
- Okay.

32:52.150 --> 32:53.519
Hi.
- I'm okay.

32:53.520 --> 32:55.333
- Okay, let me, here we go.

32:56.890 --> 32:58.557
There, a little bit.

32:59.510 --> 33:00.510
Okay.

33:08.460 --> 33:10.063
- Where is Owen?

33:11.500 --> 33:12.559
- He's out.

33:12.560 --> 33:14.159
He'll be back shortly.

33:14.160 --> 33:15.633
He's just getting a box.

33:17.810 --> 33:19.679
- But when will he be back?

33:19.680 --> 33:21.563
- Oh, well,

33:22.520 --> 33:24.393
when he gets a box.

33:25.410 --> 33:27.989
He's been out for around two hours.

33:27.990 --> 33:30.023
He should be back any minute.

33:31.040 --> 33:33.577
You can stay here until he gets back.

33:35.053 --> 33:36.443
- You are so nice.

33:39.610 --> 33:40.610
- So.

33:42.190 --> 33:45.039
How long have you known Owen?

33:45.040 --> 33:46.440
Or, where did you meet Owen?

33:48.934 --> 33:52.990
- I met him on a street
playin' the guitar.

33:54.896 --> 33:55.979
- Hm, lovely.

33:57.430 --> 33:59.312
Yeah, wow.

33:59.313 --> 34:04.049
Well, how long have you two been together?

34:04.050 --> 34:05.133
Ooh, careful.

34:06.783 --> 34:08.243
- Only one year.

34:10.489 --> 34:13.668
But, I, I can't find him.

34:13.670 --> 34:17.743
- Yeah, yeah, he's been
kind of on his own recently.

34:18.710 --> 34:19.710
Poor guy.

34:23.580 --> 34:25.549
- Why does he need boxes?

34:25.550 --> 34:28.179
- He had this lovely idea

34:28.179 --> 34:32.839
to take his guitar and
move to some random village

34:32.840 --> 34:34.688
and live with the locals to get away

34:34.690 --> 34:38.983
from modern society and the
environment, major cities.

34:40.221 --> 34:41.228
- Ah!

34:41.230 --> 34:43.458
I can go with him!

34:43.460 --> 34:44.481
- Oh, oh!

34:44.482 --> 34:46.741
No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no.

34:46.742 --> 34:47.967
No, no, no.

34:47.969 --> 34:49.149
No, no, no, no.

34:49.150 --> 34:52.223
Maybe you can play that
when Owen gets back.

34:53.520 --> 34:56.159
Maybe you can talk him out of it.

34:56.159 --> 34:57.960
I don't think it's a very good idea.

34:58.830 --> 35:01.239
- It's a great idea!

35:01.240 --> 35:05.189
Get to play with animals
and lie in the grass,

35:05.190 --> 35:06.590
and I can be with Owen.

35:08.740 --> 35:12.589
- No, the hippie, rebellious phase thing

35:12.590 --> 35:16.203
is just not very good for Owen.

35:17.230 --> 35:18.733
- All the kids do it.

35:20.796 --> 35:22.949
- The style, the short skirts,

35:22.950 --> 35:24.313
it's not very proper.

35:25.800 --> 35:26.939
I don't know.

35:26.940 --> 35:28.529
- Owen loves my skirt,

35:28.530 --> 35:30.303
says it looks really cute.

35:31.295 --> 35:32.843
- I'm sure he does.

35:33.858 --> 35:34.858
Here.

35:36.110 --> 35:40.939
Owen needs someone to take
care of him right now.

35:40.940 --> 35:42.779
- I care, I care so much.

35:42.780 --> 35:45.699
I love, I love Owen.

35:45.700 --> 35:48.379
I love him, but, I don't know

35:48.380 --> 35:49.893
how to get him to love me.

35:51.430 --> 35:55.149
- Well, sometimes boys,

35:55.150 --> 35:59.839
boys just can't see
when a girl likes them.

35:59.840 --> 36:02.419
Sometimes the girl has
to put effort into it

36:02.420 --> 36:06.339
and make some effort and
show him what he's missing.

36:06.340 --> 36:10.139
You could do what you did to me.

36:10.140 --> 36:11.935
I'm sure he'd love that.

36:13.095 --> 36:14.129
Ooh.

36:14.130 --> 36:15.380
Here, let's lay you down.

36:46.145 --> 36:49.665
- Owen, is there something
you'd like to tell me?

36:54.280 --> 36:55.280
Owen.

36:58.477 --> 37:00.163
Is there something you wanna tell me?

37:01.778 --> 37:02.979
Owen!

37:02.980 --> 37:03.980
- No.

37:07.030 --> 37:08.130
- Where have you been?

37:10.760 --> 37:14.189
- A habitat village, McGonagall Commune.

37:14.190 --> 37:15.120
- You're lying.

37:15.121 --> 37:16.769
I went there and you weren't there.

37:16.770 --> 37:18.909
- Maybe you went somewhere
else that I've been.

37:18.910 --> 37:19.743
- Where?

37:19.744 --> 37:22.659
- I don't know, State Dayton Commune.

37:22.660 --> 37:23.707
- State Dayton.

37:29.980 --> 37:32.639
Owen, tell me, how many secrets
are you keeping from me?

37:32.640 --> 37:34.509
Dayton Commune, Route Commune,

37:34.510 --> 37:36.919
I went to all of them
and you were at none!

37:36.920 --> 37:38.383
I mean, where did you go?

37:40.580 --> 37:41.980
- Where do you think I went?

37:43.373 --> 37:46.543
- I don't know, maybe to see another girl.

37:46.544 --> 37:47.956
- Yeah, what girl?

37:47.957 --> 37:49.529
- I don't know, you tell me.

37:49.530 --> 37:52.709
- Well, there is no girl.

37:52.710 --> 37:54.157
- I think you're lying.

37:55.363 --> 37:57.349
Did you just push me?

37:57.350 --> 37:58.183
- You know, you asked for it.

37:58.184 --> 37:59.559
I never wanted to get married.

37:59.560 --> 38:01.629
- Do the words I love
you mean nothing to you?

38:01.630 --> 38:04.299
- Grab the keys, get your stuff, and go.

38:04.300 --> 38:05.133
- No!

38:05.133 --> 38:06.060
We can make this work.

38:06.061 --> 38:07.176
We can just start over.

38:07.177 --> 38:09.249
- No, it's done, it is over.

38:09.250 --> 38:10.489
- No, just break it off
with the other girl.

38:10.490 --> 38:12.090
We can still be together.
- No.

38:13.370 --> 38:14.370
I don't want to.

38:15.170 --> 38:16.520
- So there is another girl.

38:19.610 --> 38:20.610
- Yeah.

38:22.520 --> 38:23.870
- I can't live without you.

38:25.260 --> 38:26.989
- Well, I don't need you.

38:26.990 --> 38:29.209
- Look, I know you need your space,

38:29.210 --> 38:30.639
but you need to take responsibility.

38:30.640 --> 38:31.520
You need to grow up!

38:31.521 --> 38:32.789
- Just go.
- No, I--

38:32.790 --> 38:33.790
- Leave!

38:37.633 --> 38:40.169
I don't usually fight women.

38:40.170 --> 38:41.889
Leave before I change my mind.

38:41.890 --> 38:43.723
- You're sick.

39:23.370 --> 39:24.370
- Who are you?

39:28.099 --> 39:29.099
What?

39:30.727 --> 39:32.213
What, what, you wanna fight?

39:33.970 --> 39:34.970
Bring it.

39:37.471 --> 39:39.021
- You think that's what I want?

39:39.889 --> 39:40.722
I'll tell you what I want.

39:40.723 --> 39:43.209
I want you to show Sarah some respect!

39:43.210 --> 39:44.043
- How do you know Sarah?

39:44.044 --> 39:45.069
- Do you love her?
- No.

39:45.070 --> 39:46.559
- Why not?
- I, I don't know.

39:46.560 --> 39:48.895
Is there a law that
says I have to love her?

39:48.896 --> 39:49.896
Oh, Jesus!

39:55.730 --> 39:57.039
Guy?
- No.

39:57.040 --> 39:58.419
- Guy, you're Guy!

39:58.420 --> 40:00.573
Guy, how are you?

40:03.140 --> 40:04.337
It's good to see you.

40:06.207 --> 40:08.109
How have you been?

40:08.110 --> 40:09.159
- Fine.
- Yeah?

40:09.160 --> 40:10.329
What's it, five years?

40:10.330 --> 40:11.679
- Yeah, man.
- Oh my God.

40:11.680 --> 40:12.823
Where have you been?

40:14.566 --> 40:15.566
- Whoa!

40:17.062 --> 40:18.538
- What?

40:18.539 --> 40:19.636
- Owen.

40:19.637 --> 40:21.136
- Oh, when we were kids!
- Yes, of course.

40:21.137 --> 40:23.399
- Oh my, I forgot about that.

40:23.400 --> 40:24.599
That's disgusting.
- Yeah, I know.

40:24.600 --> 40:25.860
- That's a nasty...

40:26.930 --> 40:28.551
- No, thanks, I'm tryin' to quit.

40:28.552 --> 40:29.385
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

40:29.386 --> 40:31.439
- How long's that been lasting?

40:31.440 --> 40:33.703
- It's been a week.

40:35.400 --> 40:36.523
So you and Sarah, huh?

40:37.630 --> 40:39.029
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

40:39.030 --> 40:39.920
- Where's she again?

40:39.921 --> 40:41.249
- What's that?
- She's gone?

40:41.250 --> 40:43.609
- Yeah, yeah, well, we got in a little--

40:43.610 --> 40:44.906
- Ooh.
- Yeah, a little tussle.

40:44.907 --> 40:47.099
- A tussle, yeah, she said that, yeah.

40:47.100 --> 40:49.979
- Yeah, yeah, it's all right.

40:49.980 --> 40:51.587
She'll come back.

40:51.588 --> 40:53.089
- Okay, great, so you talked to her

40:53.090 --> 40:54.659
and she'll be back, that's good.

40:54.660 --> 40:56.579
- I mean, she always does.

40:56.580 --> 40:57.659
She loves me.

40:57.660 --> 40:58.719
- She loves you.
- Yeah, of course.

40:58.720 --> 40:59.789
- Of course, yeah, you
guys love each other

40:59.790 --> 41:01.119
so she'll be back.

41:01.120 --> 41:02.680
- No, I mean, well she loves me.

41:04.170 --> 41:05.470
- You don't love her back.

41:07.393 --> 41:08.390
- I don't know.

41:08.390 --> 41:09.390
No.

41:10.740 --> 41:11.759
- What's not to love?

41:11.760 --> 41:15.777
I mean, she's beautiful,
she's kind, she cooks.

41:15.778 --> 41:17.189
Oooh, so good.

41:17.190 --> 41:18.190
Right?

41:21.280 --> 41:22.349
Okay.
- All right.

41:22.350 --> 41:23.940
- All right, I'll hold it.
- Hey.

41:27.864 --> 41:29.169
- No, you know what, no, no, it's okay.

41:29.170 --> 41:30.804
I'll--
- You're just gonna hold it?

41:30.805 --> 41:32.417
- Yeah, it's not--
- All right, sure.

41:32.418 --> 41:35.119
- I'll hold it like this.
- Okay, sure.

41:35.120 --> 41:36.699
- Where was I?

41:36.700 --> 41:37.999
Right.

41:38.000 --> 41:40.009
Imagine, you come home, your wife, Sarah,

41:40.010 --> 41:42.599
is in the kitchen cooking you some dinner,

41:42.600 --> 41:44.749
and your boys are out
front mowin' the lawn,

41:44.750 --> 41:45.853
playing some ball.

41:46.900 --> 41:47.929
It's a dream come true.

41:47.930 --> 41:50.599
- A dream until, you know,
your wife and kids leave you,

41:50.600 --> 41:52.150
and then what are you gonna do?

41:52.990 --> 41:56.199
- Well, why would they
leave you if you love them?

41:56.200 --> 41:57.239
- Hypothetically, you know.

41:57.240 --> 41:59.949
Like, what if they leave
you, then what do you do?

41:59.950 --> 42:01.939
- So you're gonna cut out
that entire part of your life

42:01.940 --> 42:03.313
because of a what if?

42:05.400 --> 42:07.329
- Well, I mean, if love's a tragedy

42:07.330 --> 42:09.009
why even start?

42:09.010 --> 42:10.539
- Owen, you're only gonna
get the life you want

42:10.540 --> 42:12.553
if you take the risks.

42:12.554 --> 42:13.554
- Okay.

42:16.230 --> 42:17.343
- And she loves you.

42:18.840 --> 42:21.279
And you leading her on like this is,

42:21.280 --> 42:22.280
it's not right, man.

42:23.400 --> 42:24.889
- Well, don't tell me what to do.

42:24.890 --> 42:25.890
- Yeah, well...

42:27.759 --> 42:28.592
I'll tell you what, pal.

42:28.593 --> 42:30.160
Since you're too much of a pansy,

42:33.010 --> 42:36.549
I'll do it, so you don't have to.

42:36.550 --> 42:37.969
- You'll do what?
- I'll live the dream.

42:37.970 --> 42:40.559
I'll have the girl, I'll have the kids.

42:40.560 --> 42:41.560
I'll marry Sarah.

42:42.500 --> 42:44.679
- You'll, you'll marry Sarah.

42:44.680 --> 42:45.781
- Yeah, I will.

42:45.782 --> 42:46.615
- There's gonna be a problem there,

42:46.616 --> 42:48.149
is that Sarah loves me, so--

42:48.150 --> 42:50.043
- I guess I'll have to take that risk.

42:53.247 --> 42:54.297
- All right, get out.

42:55.920 --> 42:56.989
Get the fuck outta my house.

42:56.990 --> 42:58.298
- Oh, come on, Owen, you don't wanna--

42:58.299 --> 43:00.299
- Get the fuck out, get out of my house!

43:02.030 --> 43:03.030
Now.

43:04.897 --> 43:05.897
- Fine.

43:16.780 --> 43:17.780
- Hey.

44:11.330 --> 44:14.153
- Hey, Linda.
- Hi!

44:16.399 --> 44:19.439
Ooh, look at you!
- You look great.

44:19.440 --> 44:21.949
- Thank you, you too.

44:21.950 --> 44:22.959
- So what do you think?

44:22.960 --> 44:26.169
- Oh, I love it, yeah.
- Great.

44:26.170 --> 44:27.329
- It's perfect.

44:27.330 --> 44:28.230
Thank you, so much--
- My pleasure.

44:28.231 --> 44:29.849
- For letting me stay here.

44:29.850 --> 44:30.830
- Owen is out of town right now

44:30.831 --> 44:32.419
for a couple of months,
and you can stay here

44:32.420 --> 44:33.909
while he's gone.

44:33.910 --> 44:35.749
And when he gets back, I promise

44:35.750 --> 44:38.300
I'll help you find somewhere else to live.

44:38.301 --> 44:39.339
- Okay.

44:39.340 --> 44:41.499
Well, if I can't,

44:41.500 --> 44:43.609
do you think I can maybe stay with you?

44:43.610 --> 44:45.389
Look, I promise I will pay rent.

44:45.390 --> 44:49.773
- It's not that, it's just, my fiancee.

44:50.870 --> 44:51.703
- Oh.
- Yeah.

44:51.704 --> 44:53.999
I wouldn't want her to, you know,

44:54.000 --> 44:57.179
get the wrong idea about who you are,

44:57.180 --> 45:00.039
how we met, how we know
each other, stuff like that.

45:00.040 --> 45:01.392
- You're afraid of your fiancee?

45:01.393 --> 45:03.199
- I am not afraid.

45:03.200 --> 45:04.200
I respect her.

45:05.550 --> 45:07.279
- Okay.
- Okay.

45:07.280 --> 45:10.359
- Well, it was just
'till I can find a place.

45:10.360 --> 45:12.949
- Okay, we'll see.

45:12.950 --> 45:14.013
So where you been?

45:14.965 --> 45:16.840
- Oh, traveling.

45:16.841 --> 45:21.173
Got a little caught up in the
whole hippie culture thing.

45:22.090 --> 45:25.253
So, I got a little lonely.

45:26.210 --> 45:27.379
Yeah.

45:27.380 --> 45:31.739
Thought I'd go back to my
roots and maybe settle down

45:31.740 --> 45:33.099
and start a family.

45:33.100 --> 45:34.499
- Well, you're lucky.

45:34.500 --> 45:37.009
There's a lotta great guys in this city.

45:37.010 --> 45:38.717
- Are they like you?

45:38.718 --> 45:41.743
